name: Warung Tarzan
address: Jl. Pura Lempuyang, Tri Buana, Kec. Abang, Kabupaten Karangasem, Bali 80852, Indonesia
review 1: A wonderful little family restaurant. The service was joyful, the food was delicious, and the setting was homely. I came here in a group of eight friends and it was one of the most entertaining evenings of our trip. Suksma kawan kawanku!
review 2: Good vegetarian food. Beautiful gardens and super friendly service. They even left to fetch something fresh from the store for us.
review 3: Super nice warung in the middle of the jungle. Never seen so much love and creativity put into the decoration. Everything is made of things you get out of the jungle. The food is made just in front of you and tastes very well. Very nice personal. I would definitely recommend to a friend.
review 4: Good food (although the poor choice) and abundant portions. The garden is a magic place of peace and the view on the jungle is amazing.
review 5: Excellent Balinese food, very nice atmosphere, friendly hosts, great walkway terrace, creative design by the host.  After visiting Lempuyang Temple, this is a great choice to eat, drink fresh drinks, share impressions and relax!  I highly recommend!  Many thanks to the friendly family!  God bless you! üôè
